President Obama has nominated Zachary Thomas Fardon to serve as the United States Attorney for the Northern District of Illinois. Fardon is currently a partner at the law firm Latham & Watkins and serves as the Chair of the Litigation Department in their Chicago office. He previously served as the First Assistant United States Attorney in the Middle District of Tennessee from 2003 to 2006 and as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Northern District of Illinois from 1997 to 2003. Fardon began his legal career as an Assistant Public Defender in the Nashville Metropolitan Public Defenderâ€™s Office and as an associate at the law firm King & Spalding. He received his J.D. from Vanderbilt Law School in 1992 and his B.A. from Vanderbilt University in 1988. President Obama expressed confidence in Fardon's commitment to justice and his ability to serve the people of Illinois with excellence.